name: Firebird 5.0.2
body:
### Improvements

- Add `AUTO RELEASE TEMP BLOBID` transaction option ([#8323](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/pull/8323))
- Make trace use HEX representation for parameter values ​​of types `[VAR]CHAR CHARACTER SET OCTETS` and `[VAR]BINARY`([#8356](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8356))
- Report unique usernames for `isc_info_user_names` ([#8353](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8353))
- Collect network statistics and make it available for the user applications ([#8310](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/pull/8310))
- Wire protocol improvement: prefetch blob info and some data when open blob ([#8307](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/pull/8307))
- NULLs should be skipped during index navigation when there's no lower bound and matched conditions are known to ignore NULLs ([#8291](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8291))
- Reorganize public headers ([#8273](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/pull/8273))
- Win_SSPI plug-in uses NTLM ([#8256](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8256))
- Add generated files for OO API for C language to distribution ([#8197](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8197))
- Cardinality estimation should use primary record versions only ([#8161](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8161))
- Database restore must make every effort on activating deferred indexes ([#7269](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/7269))

More details can be found in the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/blob/v5.0-release/CHANGELOG.md).

name: Firebird 4.0.5
body:
### Improvements

- Ensure the standalone CS listener on Linux uses the _SO_REUSEADDR_ socket option ([#8181](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/pull/8181))
- Added shutdown handler for _Classic Server_ ([#8165](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/pull/8165))
- More efficient evaluation of expressions like `RDB$DB_KEY <= ?` after mass delete ([#8104](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8104))
- Make protocol schemes case-insensitive ([#8066](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8066))
- Improve conflict resolution on replica when table have both primary and unique keys ([#8042](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8042))
- Better cardinality estimation when empty data pages exist ([#8030](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8030))
- Remove _gfix -cache_ option ([#8010](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/8010))
- Update Windows distributions with _zlib_ version 1.3.1 ([#7978](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/7978))
- Make _TempCacheLimit_ setting to be per-database (not per-attachment) for _SuperClassic_ ([#7928](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/7928))
- Improve performance with time zones ([#7854](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/7854))

More details can be found in the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/blob/v4.0.5/CHANGELOG.md).

name: Firebird 5.0.0
body:
Firebird 5.0 introduces many improvements without any changes in architecture or operation, the
most important are:

- Parallel (multi-threaded) operation for backup/restore, sweep and index creation
- Partial indices
- SKIP LOCKED clause for SELECT WITH LOCK, UPDATE and DELETE statements
- Inline minor ODS upgrade
- Compiled statement cache
- PSQL and SQL profiler
- Support for WHEN NOT MATCHED BY SOURCE for MERGE statement
- Support multiple rows for DML RETURNING
- New built-in functions and packages
- Denser record-level compression
- Network support for scrollable cursors 

The final release does not include any user-visible changes compared to the Release Candidate 2.

All the changes across the Beta and RC stages can be found in the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/blob/v5.0.0/CHANGELOG.md).

[Release Notes](https://firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/release_notes/Firebird-5.0.0-ReleaseNotes.pdf) | [Binary Packages](https://firebirdsql.org/en/firebird-5-0-0/)

name: Firebird 5.0.0 RC1
body:
### New features and improvements

- Use _ParallelWorkers_ setting from _firebird.conf_ as default for all parallelised operations (#7682)
- Make Android port (client / embedded) work inside apps (#7469)
- Add support for `QUARTER` to `EXTRACT`, `FIRST_DAY` and `LAST_DAY` (#5959)
- Better processing and optimization if `IN <list>` predicates (#7707)
- Make trace config parser resolve symlinks in database file path in trace configuration (#7692)
- Getting the current `DECFLOAT ROUND/TRAPS` settings (#7642)
- Allow nested parenthesized joined table (#7576)
- Optimize creation of expression and partial indices (#7559)
- Add ability to query current value of parallel workers for an attachment (#7536)
- Add _COMPILE_ trace events for procedures/functions/triggers (#7466)
- Add _REPLICA MODE_ to the output of the _isql_ `SHOW DATABASE` command (#7425)
- Surface internal optimization modes (all rows vs first rows) at the SQL and configuration levels (#7405)
- Make ability to add comment to mapping (`COMMENT ON MAPPING ... IS ...`) (#7046)

More details can be found in the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/blob/v5.0.0-RC1/CHANGELOG.md).

name: Firebird 3.0.4
body:
### What's new
- Add context variables with compression and encryption status of current connection
- Enhance dynamic libraries loading related error messages
- Provide name of UDF function for "arithmetic exception, numeric overflow, or string truncation"
- Support auth_plugin_list DPB/SPB item from application to client
- Forward-compatible expressions LOCALTIME and LOCALTIMESTAMP
- Remove the restriction on create/delete, enable/disable the user-defined indexes in system tables
- 66 bugs fixed

[Release Notes](http://www.firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/release_notes/html/en/3_0/rlsnotes30.html) | [Quick Start Guide](http://www.firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/reference_manuals/user_manuals/html/qsg3.html) | [Binary Packages](http://www.firebirdsql.org/en/firebird-3-0-4/)

name: Firebird 3.0.3
body:
### What's new
- Make faster engine response on cancel\shutdown signals when scanning long list of pointer pages
- Access to the name of DB encryption key
- Avoid UPDATE of RDB$DATABASE by ALTER DATABASE statement when possible
- When database validation fixes "orphan page" errors it now adjusts "lowest free page" marker (pip_min) on corresponding PIP, if necessary
- Consider equivalence classes for index navigation
- Allow unused Common Table Expressions
- Make flush of big number of dirty pages faster
- Avoid serialization of isc_attach_database calls issued by EXECUTE STATEMENT implementation
- GSTAT output now includes datetime of analysis
- Improve physical backup merge stage performance, especially with huge page cache
- Provide info about database (or alias) which was in use during "Error during sweep: connection shutdown"
- Improve ALTER DOMAIN performance with many dependencies
- Restore of pre ODS 11.1 database can leave RDB$RELATION_TYPE null
- Database backup using Nbackup is now faster when directed to NAS over SMB protocol
- Estimate the actual record compression ratio in the optimizer
- Add details on compression and crypt status of connection (fb_info_conn_flags) to getInfo() API call
- 68 bugs fixed

[Release Notes](http://www.firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/release_notes/html/en/3_0/rlsnotes30.html) | [Quick Start Guide](http://www.firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/reference_manuals/user_manuals/html/qsg3.html) | [Binary Packages](http://www.firebirdsql.org/en/firebird-3-0-3/)

name: Firebird 3.0.2
body:
### What's new
- Provide ability to filter out info and warnings from trace log
- Enhance control upon ability to share database crypt key between attachments in SS
- Cache physical numbers of often used data pages to reduce number of fetches of pointer pages
- Read-only transactions in SuperServer could avoid immediate write of Header and TIP pages after change
- Make database name available to crypt plugin
- Enable nested keys in plugin configuration
- Build the Linux code with --enable-binreloc and create an option in the installer to install in different locations than /opt/firebird
- Trace: provide filter to INCLUDE / EXCLUDE errors by their mnemonical names
- Support BETWEEN predicate for select expressions
- Add support for Windows 8/2012 fast/low-latency "TCP Loopback Fast Path" functionality
- Port for Linux/m68k
- Android port (arm32)
- libfbclient.so for Android (x86/x86-64/arm64)
- 42 bugs fixed

[Release Notes](http://www.firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/release_notes/html/en/3_0/rlsnotes30.html) | [Quick Start Guide](http://www.firebirdsql.org/file/documentation/reference_manuals/user_manuals/html/qsg3.html) | [Binary Packages](http://www.firebirdsql.org/en/firebird-3-0-2/)
